Stupid movie. Made me laugh though. Leslie Mann and Paul Rudd are good together.

Damn that food looked good. They made me want to visit or live there too. I’d stop equalizing too if I found a nice Italian village with free fish and a nice doctor guy who lets me live at his house. Decent movie all things considered. Much more violent than I thought it would be although it’s kind of underwhelming for a final chapter of an action franchise.

A perfectly fine, safe, American ass, feel good movie. It goes exactly as you expect. Crowe is crowing it up. Giamatti is also giamatting. Nothing wrong with it it’s just not exciting. The choppy slow mo stuff and the overall shot on a soundstage look feels so lame and lacking any style.

Great movie. Everyone is ripped but Zac Efron is a literal monster holy shit. All around really well done. Love the silly wrestling visuals and that warm film glow. The way they depict this family cursed with tragedy after tragedy and the toxic masculine pride from their father’s tyrannical relentless search for perfection is pretty brilliant, although the out comes are a little hard to believe in a 2 hour runtime regardless of it being true. First rewatch since 2015 and I really loved it. Poor Things made me want to revisit his older work that I saw years ago and I think I saw this first. I didn’t remember this being so funny but I was laughing a lot. The whole part with the hand signals was hilarious. This one feels very similar to dogtooth with the sudden shifts in tone from comedy to uncomfortable violence. Also the entire concept resonated with me more this…

I loved the way things looked and felt in this world. Ex: the suicide robot running on the bridge after saying it’s been a pleasure to serve you. Movie: Rebel Moon - Part One: A Child of Fire
Review: Slowwwwwww mooooooootion. This is spartaaaa.This is sort of a movie yeah. Technically a motion picture. It’s all boring regurgitated A.I. scripted blurry background bright light cgi garbage with characters named like general boobo and alasanadi spinky. I can’t imagine Zack Snyder or anyone for that matter can legitimately sit down and be enthralled or even entertained by this. Especially in this day and age where we have of course Star Wars and new blade runner and now new dune…

Wow this is really something. Makes sense this won the palme. Up there with the best of 2023 for me.Probably the best courtroom drama ever? Just impeccably written through and through. Characters feel like fully realized people with lives and intricacies and things you can’t ever know about them. The child acting from Milo Machado Graner is incredible. Incredibly Netflix cheesy coded but still got me a bit by the end, I’m a sucker for a paternal sad movie. Jason Sudeikis is the least cool guy ever with these fits trying to act like he’s a cool music guy. Also that band he’s trying to recruit is hilariously lame. Cold play and arcade fire are mentioned as cool music. Live lighting crashes has a feature though and that’s sick. Elizabeth Olsen is so god damn likeable. Ed Harris is a total asshole.
